Package RequestResult

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicSuccessResponse
    The most basic success response has only a message and boolean success value.
    ErrorResponse
    Every error response is the same.
    EventService
    Returns event object(s)
    EventsSuccessResponse
    Models a response for ALL events for ALL family members of the current user.
    EventSuccessResponse
    Models a single Event object with the specified ID.
    LoadRequest
    Clears all data from the database (just like the /clear API), and then loads the posted user, person, and event data into the database.
    LoginRequest
    Logs in the user and returns an auth token.
    LoginSuccessResponse
    Return auth token after login
    PersonsSuccessResponse
    Model for ALL family members of the current user.
    PersonSuccessResponse
    Model for the single Person object with the specified ID.
    RegisterRequest
    Creates a new user account, generates 4 generations of ancestor data for the new user, logs the user in, and returns an auth token.
    RegisterSuccessResponse
    return credentials and auth token
    Response
    General response model.
